---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
const lastUpdated = "April 2026";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Use"
  description="Terms for The Van Guide: how editorial content and directory listings can be used, plus disclaimers, affiliate disclosures, and user responsibilities."
>
  <section class="container-read py-10 md:py-24">
    <div class="eyebrow mb-4">Terms</div>
    <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-5xl leading-tight mb-6">Terms of Use</h1>
    <p class="font-sans-ui text-sm mb-10" style="color: var(--color-text-subtle);">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        By visiting The Van Guide, you agree to these terms. They're written to be readable.
      </p>

      <h2>Editorial content is general information, not professional advice</h2>
      <p>
        Articles on insurance, registration, taxation, safety, and legal topics are researched from primary sources and reflect our best understanding at the time of writing. They are <strong>not</strong> legal, financial, or tax advice. Insurance and DMV rules change frequently. Before making a decision with real financial or legal consequences, verify current requirements directly with the relevant carrier, agency, or a licensed professional.
      </p>

      <h2>Builder directory</h2>
      <p>
        Listings in the builder directory are based on public information and our own review process. A listing is not an endorsement. The Van Guide is not party to any transaction between you and a builder. Due your own diligence — references, site visits, signed contracts, payment terms — before committing money to any build.
      </p>

